1
00:00:11,101 --> 00:00:13,057
(Music)

2
00:00:14,778 --> 00:00:17,278
Anonyma

3
00:00:24,447 --> 00:00:28,338
A Woman in Berlin

4
00:00:33,181 --> 00:00:36,014
(woman's voice)
Who would've thought that?

5
00:00:37,021 --> 00:00:40,616
On April 16th 1945 the time had come.

6
00:00:42,221 --> 00:00:45,019
The Russian army had surrounded Berlin

7
00:00:45,119 --> 00:00:47,818
and now they were heading
towards the Reichstag.

8
00:00:49,901 --> 00:00:54,019
On this day,
you could see the sun behind the clouds,

9
00:00:54,141 --> 00:00:58,100
and the smell of lilac
wafted through all the smoke.

10
00:01:02,181 --> 00:01:04,741
How to start?

11
00:01:04,861 --> 00:01:07,819
How to find the right words?

12
00:01:09,981 --> 00:01:13,018
I've been a journalist,
I've traveled 12 countries.

13
00:01:13,141 --> 00:01:15,356
Been living in Moscow,
Paris and London.

14
00:01:15,357 --> 00:01:17,737
I really liked to stay
in Paris and London.

15
00:01:19,221 --> 00:01:23,976
I decided to come back.
I wanted to be part of it.

16
00:01:28,181 --> 00:01:31,059
My name doesn't matter.

17
00:01:31,181 --> 00:01:35,174
I am one of the many who fervently
believed in our country's future.

18
00:01:35,941 --> 00:01:38,899
Doubts?
Only weak persons had doubts.

19
00:01:39,021 --> 00:01:41,363
(Gerd) Warsaw, Brussels, Paris.
We're always winning.

20
00:01:41,364 --> 00:01:43,856
The Russians don't have a leader.

21
00:01:43,981 --> 00:01:45,856
When they finally come to their senses,

22
00:01:45,857 --> 00:01:48,452
we are already knocking at
their front door in Moscow.

23
00:01:50,661 --> 00:01:54,540
Pardon our pushiness,
but it's war after all.

24
00:01:54,661 --> 00:01:56,195
Gerd hated railway stations.

25
00:01:56,196 --> 00:01:59,098
When he left, the sound of
his boots filled the house.

26
00:02:00,901 --> 00:02:03,415
We were certain to do the right thing,

27
00:02:03,416 --> 00:02:05,467
we breathed the same
air as everybody else.

28
00:02:05,468 --> 00:02:06,259
We were part of this.

29
00:02:07,581 --> 00:02:09,326
And then he takes off my coat and says:

30
00:02:09,327 --> 00:02:12,097
The Russians have no idea
what's coming towards them.

31
00:02:13,181 --> 00:02:17,538
So we were heading towards the
Sorbonne and chatting away in French.

32
00:02:17,661 --> 00:02:21,540
He thought that I was one
of those tall blond Swedes.

33
00:02:21,661 --> 00:02:25,540
Then I made a double step
to match my stride to his.

34
00:02:25,661 --> 00:02:29,620
That's when he stopped and said:
"Ah, a daughter of the Fuhrer"

35
00:02:30,421 --> 00:02:33,970
That was the end of the acquaintance.
What a pity.

36
00:02:34,941 --> 00:02:38,900
Hold on. I... I'd like to...
Stop the music, please.

37
00:02:41,581 --> 00:02:46,132
I would like for us all
to share this moment,

38
00:02:46,261 --> 00:02:49,810
this wonderful evening,
with our husbands

39
00:02:49,981 --> 00:02:53,860
who are stationed
somewhere all over Europe.

40
00:03:01,901 --> 00:03:03,937
(Explosions)

41
00:03:11,061 --> 00:03:12,892
Get lost!

42
00:03:13,021 --> 00:03:14,773
Run, run!

43
00:03:15,101 --> 00:03:16,250
Get away!

44
00:03:18,181 --> 00:03:21,969
(woman) Go away!
(officer) Houses on the right. Fan out.

45
00:03:22,101 --> 00:03:24,057
(honking)

46
00:03:24,461 --> 00:03:26,417
(Soldiers singing)

47
00:03:32,901 --> 00:03:34,857
Come here, damn it!

48
00:03:35,381 --> 00:03:37,815
(child)
Mummy, where are you?

49
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:41,134
Come on. Hurry.

50
00:04:04,861 --> 00:04:07,421
(Soldier)
Away. Go away.

51
00:04:09,341 --> 00:04:12,413
Open fire, reload grenade.

52
00:04:13,381 --> 00:04:15,337
...and fire!

53
00:04:21,741 --> 00:04:22,969
Fire!

54
00:04:24,221 --> 00:04:25,370
Shit.

55
00:04:28,021 --> 00:04:31,570
- Wait for me.
- Watch out! Heads down.

56
00:04:32,661 --> 00:04:35,494
- There you are.
- Stop! Wait for me.

57
00:04:35,621 --> 00:04:36,610
Watch out!

58
00:04:38,541 --> 00:04:40,850
(woman)
No!

59
00:04:47,181 --> 00:04:51,140
No uniforms, no weapons,
or it's martial law.

60
00:04:51,901 --> 00:04:53,857
(Russian)

61
00:04:56,421 --> 00:04:59,254
(woman)
Felix, where are you?

62
00:05:01,821 --> 00:05:03,220
Felix?

63
00:05:03,741 --> 00:05:08,292
- Where the hell is he? Felix?
- Not a single order.

64
00:05:08,461 --> 00:05:12,420
No messages, nothing at all.
Nobody gives a shit about us.

65
00:05:12,901 --> 00:05:16,860
Felix? Lenchen, Lenchen?
Where are you, damn it?

66
00:05:17,821 --> 00:05:21,136
In Wedding district, they are already
showing their toddlers to the Russians.

67
00:05:21,236 --> 00:05:22,451
Russian pigs.

68
00:05:22,581 --> 00:05:26,733
That were the book dealers.
They sometimes speak French.

69
00:05:29,181 --> 00:05:32,093
And that's the pharmacist's widow.

70
00:05:32,221 --> 00:05:37,011
Her husband once cured Minister
Hindenburg's headache.

71
00:05:37,141 --> 00:05:38,018
That's over.

72
00:05:38,019 --> 00:05:41,817
Now you step on the face
and the arms of a dead woman

73
00:05:42,261 --> 00:05:45,219
only to get a glass of jelly.

74
00:05:48,021 --> 00:05:53,049
That's the quiet Mrs. Binder.
Musician. Her husband is MIA.

75
00:05:54,581 --> 00:05:56,537
(Screaming)

76
00:05:57,541 --> 00:06:01,659
Can someone help?
She is suffocating.

77
00:06:02,861 --> 00:06:06,740
Look at me. Look at me!

78
00:06:07,421 --> 00:06:10,970
I will write all of this down,
I will report it.

79
00:06:12,061 --> 00:06:15,019
Gerd, and you shall read it.

80
00:06:15,341 --> 00:06:18,174
May I offer you something?

81
00:06:19,901 --> 00:06:21,220
Thank you.

82
00:06:29,741 --> 00:06:32,699
From Silesia.
She won't make it.

83
00:06:54,661 --> 00:06:56,617
(Music)

84
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:18,537
Go, go, go!
Go down there, quick!

85
00:07:23,581 --> 00:07:26,539
- Mummy?
- Don't be afraid, I am here.

86
00:07:31,061 --> 00:07:32,858
They're coming.

87
00:07:37,501 --> 00:07:39,457
(Russian)

88
00:07:51,021 --> 00:07:52,249
Halt!

89
00:08:22,581 --> 00:08:27,211
(Announcement) Attention, attention.
To all the residents of this street.

90
00:08:28,581 --> 00:08:32,130
All fire arms have to be
turned in immediately.

91
00:08:33,541 --> 00:08:36,374
This is the last warning.

92
00:08:36,741 --> 00:08:39,301
Attention, attention.

93
00:08:39,621 --> 00:08:42,454
This is the last warning.

94
00:09:05,501 --> 00:09:07,457
(Russian)

95
00:09:35,082 --> 00:09:36,582
Attack!

96
00:09:50,078 --> 00:09:51,578
Upstairs!

97
00:09:52,968 --> 00:09:54,968
All the way upstairs!

98
00:10:08,102 --> 00:10:09,602
Go away! Not now!

99
00:10:09,781 --> 00:10:10,736
Attention!

100
00:10:26,261 --> 00:10:28,217
(Russian)

101
00:10:40,618 --> 00:10:42,118
I... I have...

102
00:10:44,919 --> 00:10:47,919
(whispering in Russian)

103
00:11:01,882 --> 00:11:02,882
Careful!

104
00:11:03,331 --> 00:11:05,331
Comrade Colonel.

105
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:08,623
The troops have almost
reached Potsdam station.

106
00:11:10,072 --> 00:11:13,072
But the order was to go towards
the government district!

107
00:11:16,048 --> 00:11:18,548
Understood,
Comrade Colonel.

108
00:11:22,957 --> 00:11:24,457
We'll stay here.

109
00:11:24,957 --> 00:11:26,457
Major! I thought we were
going to the Reichstag.

110
00:11:27,052 --> 00:11:28,552
No Reichstag? But why not,
we are so close.

111
00:11:29,626 --> 00:11:31,626
Screw it,
we are not staying here!

112
00:11:31,886 --> 00:11:33,886
That's an order!

113
00:11:34,936 --> 00:11:37,936
Retreat!
Secure our flank!

114
00:11:40,459 --> 00:11:41,959
Understood?

115
00:11:45,966 --> 00:11:47,966
Soldiers?
Officers?

116
00:11:49,491 --> 00:11:50,991
Weapons?

117
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:54,510
I said: Soldiers?
Officers?

118
00:11:55,621 --> 00:11:59,057
(woman)
They will see soon enough.

119
00:12:01,639 --> 00:12:03,139
Anybody got weapons?
Hand them over.

120
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:05,550
Get out!
One person at a time.

121
00:12:18,803 --> 00:12:19,803
Get out, all of you!
Move it!

122
00:12:20,541 --> 00:12:23,009
- Russian filth!
- Up!

123
00:12:27,342 --> 00:12:29,842
What... do you want?

124
00:12:36,301 --> 00:12:37,336
Russian?

125
00:12:39,122 --> 00:12:40,122
Yes.

126
00:12:45,581 --> 00:12:46,855
Russian!

127
00:12:47,861 --> 00:12:49,135
Come.

128
00:12:49,581 --> 00:12:50,536
Come.

129
00:12:51,901 --> 00:12:52,970
Eat.

130
00:12:56,181 --> 00:12:58,137
War kaput.

131
00:12:59,061 --> 00:13:00,016
Woman.

132
00:13:00,381 --> 00:13:02,736
Come! Eat.

133
00:13:04,341 --> 00:13:06,297
War kaput, woman.

134
00:13:06,355 --> 00:13:07,355
Come on.

135
00:13:08,701 --> 00:13:10,578
No fear.

136
00:13:10,701 --> 00:13:12,692
No fear.

137
00:13:21,861 --> 00:13:24,853
We will not die here.

138
00:13:45,741 --> 00:13:47,697
Bravo, come, come.

139
00:13:48,501 --> 00:13:50,014
Don't be afraid.

140
00:13:51,221 --> 00:13:52,176
Come.

141
00:13:53,141 --> 00:13:54,859
Don't shiver!

142
00:13:55,661 --> 00:13:57,094
Good! Come.

143
00:14:00,461 --> 00:14:02,417
Hey, cuties!
Come over here.

144
00:14:04,621 --> 00:14:07,454
You be nice and you'll
get something to eat.

145
00:14:12,701 --> 00:14:14,817
Potatoes. Very good.

146
00:14:57,501 --> 00:14:59,457
May I?

147
00:15:13,341 --> 00:15:15,377
(soldiers laughing)

148
00:15:18,341 --> 00:15:20,377
(Music)

149
00:15:30,181 --> 00:15:32,649
Does anybody know
how this thing works?

150
00:15:33,021 --> 00:15:34,541
You, Ukrainian,
do you know it?

151
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:38,130
There they are,
our Russian liberators.

152
00:15:38,261 --> 00:15:40,138
Full of joy.

153
00:15:40,261 --> 00:15:44,857
It seems they can hardly believe
that they've made it this far.

154
00:15:44,981 --> 00:15:47,453
I know them,
their sandals and villages.

155
00:15:47,454 --> 00:15:50,851
Their rapidly constructed new
buildings they are so proud of.

156
00:15:51,601 --> 00:15:52,301
Stop!

157
00:15:52,461 --> 00:15:55,219
They are without any constraints.

158
00:15:55,261 --> 00:15:56,296
Don't move,
asshole!

159
00:15:56,741 --> 00:15:58,459
Leave her.

160
00:16:00,541 --> 00:16:01,974
Get lost.

161
00:16:14,521 --> 00:16:16,781
Urine.
Why don't you use urine?

162
00:16:19,261 --> 00:16:20,853
That's enough!

163
00:16:21,101 --> 00:16:22,050
No, seriously...

164
00:16:22,181 --> 00:16:24,297
Your urine is much too old.

165
00:16:25,581 --> 00:16:28,857
Back in Leningrad, I put my general
back on his feet with urine...

166
00:16:30,461 --> 00:16:32,053
You storyteller!

167
00:16:32,821 --> 00:16:34,049
It's true.

168
00:16:40,141 --> 00:16:41,859
What are they doing?

169
00:16:44,581 --> 00:16:45,536
Please!

170
00:16:46,261 --> 00:16:47,376
Please!

171
00:16:48,781 --> 00:16:51,011
Have you husband?

172
00:16:52,181 --> 00:16:54,217
A husband and two children.

173
00:16:59,221 --> 00:17:01,974
Come anyway.

174
00:17:02,581 --> 00:17:07,211
Quick, quick!
(woman) Let me through! Let me through!

175
00:17:10,781 --> 00:17:13,614
No, no, you pigs.

176
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:16,460
You pigs! No!

177
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:21,620
- You don't belong here.
- I didn't do anything wrong.

178
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:22,680
Stop.

179
00:17:22,741 --> 00:17:26,220
- You filthy pigs, leave me alone!
(man) Come on, don't be so prude.

180
00:17:26,341 --> 00:17:30,220
Most fellow countrymen adeptly
saved their own hides.

181
00:17:30,341 --> 00:17:33,856
The girl from Silesia was easy prey.

182
00:17:34,281 --> 00:17:35,296
Leave!

183
00:17:36,661 --> 00:17:38,617
Mrs. Hitler.

184
00:17:42,501 --> 00:17:44,059
You slut! Where to?

185
00:17:44,141 --> 00:17:45,699
To the Fuhrer?

186
00:17:48,861 --> 00:17:52,649
Here. Quick.
Penthouse to the right. Quick! Go!

187
00:17:55,341 --> 00:17:58,060
Take this and go! Go!

188
00:17:58,341 --> 00:17:59,376
Come.

189
00:18:03,301 --> 00:18:07,533
You speak Russian.
You can't abandon me like that.

190
00:18:14,581 --> 00:18:15,616
Soldier!

191
00:18:22,381 --> 00:18:24,497
Why are you taking a woman...

192
00:18:25,381 --> 00:18:27,451
who doesn't want you?

193
00:18:28,621 --> 00:18:30,452
Willing women are unclean.

194
00:18:41,741 --> 00:18:43,732
(Door is closed)

195
00:18:50,861 --> 00:18:53,500
Open the door! Open it!

196
00:18:53,621 --> 00:18:56,579
Open the door,
you bastards! Open it!

197
00:19:22,501 --> 00:19:24,457
(Music)

198
00:19:35,501 --> 00:19:37,332
Not here.

199
00:20:00,261 --> 00:20:03,219
- Where?
- Almost there.

200
00:20:09,821 --> 00:20:12,733
Stop! Stay where you are!

201
00:20:16,741 --> 00:20:18,015
Hey you.

202
00:20:18,141 --> 00:20:19,494
Shoo shoo!

203
00:20:24,901 --> 00:20:26,334
Commander...

204
00:20:26,861 --> 00:20:28,340
I am looking for
the commanding officer.

205
00:20:28,501 --> 00:20:30,093
What's up?

206
00:20:31,461 --> 00:20:33,099
Are you in charge here?

207
00:20:33,461 --> 00:20:36,214
I... we need help.

208
00:20:42,541 --> 00:20:44,532
Are you in charge here?

209
00:20:45,861 --> 00:20:48,933
There are many in charge here.
Everybody is in charge.

210
00:20:50,421 --> 00:20:51,536
Which one do you want?

211
00:20:54,821 --> 00:20:56,300
Major, sir...

212
00:20:57,901 --> 00:21:00,461
We need your help...

213
00:21:02,541 --> 00:21:05,453
Our men are all healthy and clean.

214
00:21:07,981 --> 00:21:10,017
(car departs)

215
00:21:29,781 --> 00:21:31,737
Mrs. Hitler.

216
00:21:32,501 --> 00:21:35,334
Our country is finished.

217
00:21:36,341 --> 00:21:39,936
Gerd, do you remember your first words?

218
00:21:40,061 --> 00:21:45,340
"Give me 30 minutes and you will
never want to leave me again."

219
00:21:47,181 --> 00:21:49,172
God almighty.

220
00:22:49,021 --> 00:22:52,900
- That is the back corridor.
- The widow offered me a place to stay.

221
00:22:53,021 --> 00:22:58,095
She took me by the hand and just led me
inside her undestroyed apartment.

222
00:23:00,101 --> 00:23:06,813
- I gratefully accepted the offer.
- You can stay here for a while.

223
00:23:07,181 --> 00:23:13,017
Moving places was easy: a blouse,
a few books and notebooks.

224
00:23:13,461 --> 00:23:17,340
- You are welcome to stay.
- Thank you, I'll take your offer.

225
00:23:19,021 --> 00:23:21,057
(Russians singing)

226
00:23:29,501 --> 00:23:32,334
Take good care of yourself.

227
00:23:37,141 --> 00:23:41,100
In spite of everything, it would have
been good to have a closer look around.

228
00:23:41,661 --> 00:23:46,815
But then, we never know everything,
so that's how the story continued.

229
00:24:01,661 --> 00:24:04,494
I guess it has been
really nice here once.

230
00:24:06,501 --> 00:24:09,891
How did you find me here?

231
00:24:11,341 --> 00:24:14,299
I searched every cellar.

232
00:24:29,941 --> 00:24:31,897
How often?

233
00:24:38,341 --> 00:24:39,410
Often.

234
00:24:45,261 --> 00:24:46,614
The shores are clad in green,

235
00:24:46,661 --> 00:24:49,129
the trees are breathing
freely and deeply

236
00:24:49,261 --> 00:24:51,411
We bravely stride on and on,

237
00:24:51,741 --> 00:24:53,771
towards the final assault
in this war!

238
00:24:55,581 --> 00:24:57,492
Our path was long to reach
this day in May.

239
00:24:57,621 --> 00:25:00,010
It has cost us much
strength and courage.

240
00:25:00,181 --> 00:25:02,456
But now we are free again!

241
00:25:02,621 --> 00:25:05,499
We proudly take our positions.

242
00:25:06,621 --> 00:25:07,736
Greetings, May.

243
00:25:09,581 --> 00:25:14,176
Our soldiers and a few American weapons,
and those would be history.

244
00:25:14,177 --> 00:25:14,530
Yeah.

245
00:25:18,861 --> 00:25:20,817
(Russians cheering)

246
00:25:26,901 --> 00:25:29,853
Yesterday at the water pump,
it was my turn,

247
00:25:29,854 --> 00:25:31,099
a guy approaches me,

248
00:25:32,301 --> 00:25:36,897
two Iron Crosses and one German
Cross in Gold on his chest,

249
00:25:37,021 --> 00:25:40,980
and he gallantly takes the buckets
out of my hands. And I say:

250
00:25:41,101 --> 00:25:47,097
"How do I deserve this honor?"
and he says "We can't give up now"

251
00:25:47,701 --> 00:25:51,296
"because if the Russian
even remotely does to us

252
00:25:51,421 --> 00:25:55,300
"what we did to them
during the last four years,

253
00:25:56,021 --> 00:25:59,570
"in the near future there won't
be any living Germans left."

254
00:26:02,781 --> 00:26:05,739
"In the near future"?
Nobody talks like that.

255
00:26:12,421 --> 00:26:18,053
Hey you Slavs!
We're in Berlin! We made it!

256
00:26:30,621 --> 00:26:35,297
How do you say: Excuse me,
do you have a dictionary?

257
00:26:36,261 --> 00:26:40,334
I guess he doesn't need a
dictionary for what he wants.

258
00:26:49,781 --> 00:26:51,737
(banging)

259
00:26:54,941 --> 00:26:55,930
Lenchen!

260
00:26:56,061 --> 00:26:58,097
(unintelligible)

261
00:27:07,301 --> 00:27:09,257
Come with us!

262
00:27:09,581 --> 00:27:11,811
Come where?

263
00:27:13,061 --> 00:27:14,050
Lenchen!

264
